fsociety@root:/about $ cat about_site.md

>> About This Site

This is an unofficial Mr. Robot fan hub, created as a digital homage to the series that redefined tech thrillers.

All content, code, and style were assembled as part of a student web development project, built with WordPress and custom HTML/CSS blocks.

It's a simulation of fsociety's digital world — reimagined as a user-controlled terminal exploring characters, events, and ideology behind the 5/9 hack.

No trademarks claimed. No data stolen. Just admiration for storytelling, hacking culture, and great design.

// Created by: Kenneth Plumstead

item.title: Plot
item.dc:creator: codeitrightdaily
item.content:encoded:
Last login: Sat May 18 22:10:04 on ttys000

Elliot@fsociety-machine ~ %

fsociety@root:/plot $ cat intro.md

>> Plot Summary

Events of fsociety's first major operation: the 5/9 Hack.
All data shown below is pulled from decrypted internal logs.

fsociety@root:/plot $ ▌

Last login: Sat May 18 22:11:09 on ttys001

Elliot@fsociety-machine ~ %

fsociety@root:/plot $ cat plot_summary.log

[INIT] Elliot Alderson, cybersecurity engineer, battles social anxiety and depression.

[DISCOVERY] Recruited by Mr. Robot, the mysterious leader of fsociety.

[RECRUIT] Darlene, Mobley, Trenton, and Romero join the underground hacker collective.

[TARGET] fsociety’s goal: Take down E Corp (“Evil Corp”) and erase global debt.

[INFILTRATE] Elliot hacks Allsafe to secretly install a backdoor into E Corp servers.

[STEEL_MOUNTAIN] The crew physically infiltrates a data facility to plant malware.

[COLLISION] Elliot’s reality begins to fracture as he struggles with Mr. Robot’s identity.

[EXECUTION] The 5/9 Hack is launched, successfully crippling E Corp worldwide.

[AFTERMATH] Chaos erupts, fsociety goes viral, and Elliot begins to question everything.

fsociety@root:/plot $ ▌

item.dc:creator: codeitrightdaily
item.content:encoded:
Last login: Sat May 18 22:09:42 on ttys000

Elliot@fsociety-machine ~ %

fsociety@root:/crew $ ls

crew.txt

welcome_note.md

fsociety@root:/crew $ cat crew.txt

Elliot Alderson
Lead hacker. Disillusioned cybersecurity engineer with a moral compass buried in code.
Alias: root // Status: conflicted

Mr. Robot
The anarchist architect of fsociety. Bold, ideological, and always watching.
Alias: mr.robot // Status: volatile

Darlene
Fearless and unfiltered. Elliot’s sister and the spark behind fsociety’s loudest acts.
Alias: malware // Specialty: wireless intrusion

Mobley
Cautious coder and the moral pulse of the crew. Smart, but always looking over his shoulder.
Alias: sysadmin // Specialty: server deployment

Trenton
Brilliant and precise. Ethical hacker with a conscience. The quiet strength in fsociety.
Alias: cryptofox // Specialty: encryption

Romero
Hardware wizard and darknet plug. Knows how to make any system bleed.
Alias: bitmancer // Specialty: physical infrastructure

fsociety@root:/crew $ ▌
